    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-10-27T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-10-27T17:00:00-05:00" n="616"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d616">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.85/10–2744: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Donnelly</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-27T19:00:00-03:00"
                            >October 27, 1944—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 27—1 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3868. The Brazilian Embassy in Washington has informed Velloso<note n="16"
                        xml:id="d616fn16">Pedro Leão Velloso, Brazilian Minister for Foreign
                        Affairs.</note> that the WSA is holding up the transfer of two tankers
                    recently purchased by Brazilian interests on the grounds that Brazil has not yet
                    agreed to enter the shipping pool of the United Nations. Velloso asked me to
                    inform the Department that a committee in the Foreign Office has just completed
                    a study of the shipping pool plan and that the Ministry will recommend to
                    President Vargas that Brazil subscribe to the agreement. In view thereof he
                    hopes that the WSA will facilitate the tanker transaction.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Donnelly</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
